wiki.content:
Recorded live in 1969 at Electric Ladyland Studios in Los Angeles, this track featured Jimi Hendrix (of course), Mitch Mitchell on drums, Jack Casady on bass and Steve Winwood on Hammond organ. Sounds from a small crowd of friends can be heard in the background during the more quiet parts of the song.

track.name: Voodoo Chile
comments: The ups and downs moments are great.
According to me, the best Jimmy Hendrix song.............everrrrrrrrrrrrr
A lot of people rave about Jimi's guitar playing, and he deserves every minuet of it. But let's not forget he was also a kick-ass songwriter-case in point playing right now!
I don't think we'll ever get another guitarist on his level. Probably have to wait a couple hundred years for somebody to get close to what he did for guitarists.
